# Dev-only (loaded by `vite` dev server, NOT by `vite build`). Point the SPA
# straight at the local API so REST + WebSocket both hit the backend directly —
# this avoids a vite dev-proxy quirk where proxied WebSocket frames after the
# handshake aren't forwarded. In production the build uses a relative /api base
# served by nginx (which proxies WebSocket upgrades correctly).
VITE_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000
